OL,3,CWet February dampens retail sales amid
OL,4,CMiddle East conflict threat to
OL,5,Cconfidence
OL,7,FFebruary's wet weather dampened retail
OL,8,Fsales across the UK amid warnings that
OL,9,Fthe Middle East conflict is
OL,10,Fthreatening to halt any longer-term
OL,11,Frecovery in consumer confidence.
OL,13,FTotal UK retail sales increased by
OL,14,Fjust 1.1% year on year, against
OL,15,Falready sluggish growth last February
OL,16,Fand well below the 12-month average of
OL,17,F2.3%, according to British Retail
OL,18,FConsortium (BRC) and KPMG figures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773144742
OL,3,CWet February dampens retail sales amid
OL,4,CMiddle East conflict threat to
OL,5,Cconfidence
OL,7,FFood sales were flat in real terms at
OL,8,F2.9% ` below the 12-month average
OL,9,Fgrowth of 3.8% ` as shoppers tightened
OL,10,Ftheir belts.
OL,12,FNon-food sales fell by 0.4% overall `
OL,13,Frising in stores by 0.2% but declining
OL,14,Fby 1.3% online as households reined in
OL,15,Fspending after Christmas and January's
OL,16,Frebound.
OL,18,FHowever, Valentine's Day did provide a
OL,19,Fsmall bright spot, with jewellery,
OL,20,Fwatches and perfume performing better
OL,21,Fas consumers still treated loved ones.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773144742
OL,3,CWet February dampens retail sales amid
OL,4,CMiddle East conflict threat to
OL,5,Cconfidence
OL,7,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,8,Fsaid: "February's grey, wet weather
OL,9,Fhit retail sales hard.
OL,11,F"While retailers look to Spring and
OL,12,Fbetter weather to lift spirits and
OL,13,Frevive sales, conflict in the Middle
OL,14,FEast threatens knocking any recovery
OL,15,Foff course.
OL,17,F"Prolonged low consumer confidence
OL,18,Fadds strain on retailers already
OL,19,Ffacing mounting cost pressures, higher
OL,20,Ftaxes and a growing regulatory burden."
OL,26,@pD@GOUsD@AOUyD@AOU|D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773144742
OL,3,CWet February dampens retail sales amid
OL,4,CMiddle East conflict threat to
OL,5,Cconfidence
OL,7,FSarah Bradbury, the chief executive of
OL,8,Fanalysts IGD, said: "As March begins,
OL,9,Fthe outlook is deteriorating. The
OL,10,FOBR's latest forecast downgraded near-
OL,11,Fterm growth, whilst the conflict in
OL,12,Fthe Middle East is strengthening
OL,13,Fconcerns over fuel costs, which could
OL,14,Fimpact food price inflation, if the
OL,15,Fsituation continues."
OL,17,FIn separate figures from Barclays,
OL,18,Fcard spending grew just 1% in February
OL,19,Fas inflation and travel concerns
OL,20,Fdampened confidence.
OL,26,@pD@UOUwD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773144742
OL,3,CWet February dampens retail sales amid
OL,4,CMiddle East conflict threat to
OL,5,Cconfidence
OL,7,FSome 82% of consumers are concerned
OL,8,Fabout the impact of tensions in the
OL,9,FMiddle East on fuel costs, energy
OL,10,Fbills (81%) and inflation (78%), as
OL,11,Fwell as on food prices (76%), a poll
OL,12,Ffor the bank early this month found.
OL,14,FHowever, entertainment spending
OL,15,Fincreased by 9.9% in February ` an 11-
OL,16,Fmonth high ` with transactions peaking
OL,17,Fwhen tickets to Harry Styles's
OL,18,FTogether, Together Tour went on sale
OL,19,Fon January 30.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
